						<div class="postbody">Just got done using the Altera USB blaster on my own NESRGB board. I'd never done anything like this before, so I was thrilled that there were zero problems and it worked first try.<br /><br />I can tell you the saturated palette running on the NESRGB board looks <span style="text-decoration: underline">identical</span> to my umodded NES hooked into the same 55&quot; LCD display! I couldn't be happier with the outcome (finally screens like the title to Castlevania II have the right colors)!<br /><br />OCD 100% satisfied, and a HUGE THANK YOU to Tim for taking the time to indulge me on this obsessive goal.<br /><br /><br />BTW, I'm betting the unsaturated palette will be better for those with CRT setups, as saturation can be adjusted directly from the CRT as needed.</div>

